text: Tinea conspecta is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Alfred Philpott in 1931. However the placement of this species within the genus Tinea is in doubt. As a result, this species has been referred to as Tinea (s.l.) conspecta. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1931 Category:Tineidae Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand
title: Tinea conspecta
